race.comment: GRINGOTTS (1) won this race last year with the 58kg from an outside gate and looks to be going just as well. Gave HEADLEY GRANGE 3kg first-up for a narrow second as fav in the Alan Brown Stakes over 1400m at Rosehill. Can turn the tables from the soft draw with Rawiller retaining the ride. LORD OF BISCAY (12) two runs back have been sound, and this looks a target race with the big weight drop. Can race a little closer today and adept in all conditions. Top three player. HEADLEY GRANGE (2) has gone to a new level this prep and turned in a huge effort from the outside gate when a tenacious winner of the Alan Brown. Drawn out again and hard to knock winning form. TIME QUEST (13) proven miler retaining his zest for racing. Will relish the good tempo and produce late. The chances don't end there.
